shorewall-nft (0.0.4) unstable; urgency=medium

  * shorewall6 migrate no longer fails on the stock conntrack file. The
    conntrack helpers with no IPv6 support in the kernel (irc,
    netbios-ns, pptp, snmp, amanda) are skipped for IPv6.
  * Ship shorewall6.service, so IPv6 comes up at boot. migrate now
    enables the service for the stack it hands over.
  * migrate handles one stack at a time and warns when the other still
    needs migrating, and it clears only its own family's old iptables
    ruleset, leaving the other family's firewall in place.

 -- Dave Kempe <dave@sol1.com.au>  Wed, 08 Jul 2026 15:00:00 +0000

shorewall-nft (0.0.3) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Separate family tables. shorewall now uses table ip shorewall and
    shorewall6 uses table ip6 shorewall, so a box can run both at once
    without one deleting the other's rules, and a v4 ruleset no longer
    drops all IPv6.
  * migrate tears down the previous Shorewall iptables ruleset, so the
    old and new firewalls do not both filter at once.
  * Multi-ISP: balanced providers skip interfaces that are down instead
    of failing the whole route, and a "-" gateway routes via the device.

 -- Dave Kempe <dave@sol1.com.au>  Wed, 08 Jul 2026 12:00:00 +0000

shorewall-nft (0.0.2) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Conflict with, replace and provide shorewall6 and shorewall-core in
    addition to shorewall, so installing over a distribution Shorewall
    (whose /usr/sbin/shorewall lives in shorewall-core) does not fail on
    a file overwrite.

 -- Dave Kempe <dave@sol1.com.au>  Wed, 08 Jul 2026 00:00:00 +0000

shorewall-nft (0.0.1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Initial packaging. Shorewall-compatible firewall compiler for
    nftables, reading an existing /etc/shorewall unchanged.

 -- Dave Kempe <dave@sol1.com.au>  Tue, 07 Jul 2026 00:00:00 +0000
